**To create a flow log for a VPC**

The following ``create-flow-logs`` example creates a flow log that captures all traffic for the specified VPC. ::

    aws ec2 create-flow-logs \
        --resource-type VPC \
        --resource-ids vpc-0a60eb65b4EXAMPLE \
        --traffic-type ALL \
        --log-destination-type cloud-watch-logs \
        --log-group-name my-flow-logs

Output::

    {
        "ClientToken": "",
        "FlowLogIds": [
            "fl-0abcdef1234567890"
        ],
        "Unsuccessful": []
    }
